(crowd cheering)

774
01:01:44,993 --> 01:01:48,163
God bless you guys. Thank
you for coming up here.

775
01:01:48,455 --> 01:01:51,041
We're so proud of you.

776
01:01:51,333 --> 01:01:57,631
♪

777
01:01:57,923 --> 01:02:00,258
The Recycled Orchestra,
a group from Paraguay,

778
01:02:00,550 --> 01:02:04,179
made a stop at Saskatchewan this week
to spread entertainment and inspiration.

779
01:02:04,471 --> 01:02:06,681
(applause)

780
01:02:06,973 --> 01:02:09,351
♪

781
01:02:09,643 --> 01:02:11,723
Three shows this weekend,
first one in Winkler today.

782
01:02:11,853 --> 01:02:14,248
Two in Winnipeg tomorrow, and
then they're continuing across Canada.

783
01:02:14,272 --> 01:02:15,941
♪

784
01:02:16,233 --> 01:02:20,111
Now they're taking their
spectacle to Amsterdam.

785
01:02:20,403 --> 01:02:28,403
♪

786
01:02:29,079 --> 01:02:33,625
Queen Sofia of Spain attended a concert
this morning in Madrid's National Theater.

787
01:02:33,917 --> 01:02:37,045
The concert was performed by the
Recycled Orchestra of Cateura, Paraguay.

788
01:02:37,337 --> 01:02:43,343
So what is it that makes the difference
and allows these kids to be on the stage?

789
01:02:43,635 --> 01:02:44,928
It's opportunity.

790
01:02:45,220 --> 01:02:47,430
(applause)

791
01:02:47,722 --> 01:02:55,722
♪

792
01:02:58,817 --> 01:03:00,986
Please welcome the
Recycled Orchestra of Cateura!

793
01:03:01,278 --> 01:03:03,029
(applause)

794
01:03:03,321 --> 01:03:04,447
♪

795
01:03:04,739 --> 01:03:07,158
I always feel like
I'm living in a dream.

796
01:03:07,450 --> 01:03:14,249
♪

797
01:03:14,541 --> 01:03:16,835
But that eventually
I'll wake up.

798
01:03:17,127 --> 01:03:20,672
♪

799
01:03:20,964 --> 01:03:24,676
Who would have thought that the Recycled
Orchestra of Cateura would go so far?

800
01:03:24,968 --> 01:03:27,679
They are preparing for a
tour throughout South America

801
01:03:27,971 --> 01:03:29,472
with the heavy
metal group Metallica.

802
01:03:30,640 --> 01:03:33,518
Cateura! Cateura! Cateura!

803
01:03:33,810 --> 01:03:36,313
♪

804
01:03:36,604 --> 01:03:38,982
That's when one of the
girls said we touched the sky.

805
01:03:39,274 --> 01:03:45,113
♪

806
01:03:45,405 --> 01:03:46,698
(speaking in Spanish)

807
01:03:46,990 --> 01:03:51,661
♪

808
01:03:51,953 --> 01:03:54,289
(raindrops plunking)

809
01:03:59,836 --> 01:04:05,300
In Paraguay, major floods have displaced
thousands of people in recent weeks.

810
01:04:05,592 --> 01:04:08,092
According to the
latest count, there are

811
01:04:08,104 --> 01:04:11,056
around 43,000 families
affected in the country.

812
01:04:11,348 --> 01:04:17,354
According to the National Emergency Agency,
this number represents 214,000 refugees.

813
01:04:17,645 --> 01:04:21,191
This is the largest
flood in over 20 years.

814
01:04:22,942 --> 01:04:27,906
Families in Cateura are
being forced from their homes

815
01:04:28,198 --> 01:04:29,616
due to the flooding.

816
01:04:29,908 --> 01:04:32,035
♪

817
01:04:32,327 --> 01:04:35,705
The flood refugees are
living in makeshift camps

818
01:04:35,997 --> 01:04:40,377
and in unsafe structures of plywood
and plastic in streets, parks, and plazas.

819
01:04:40,668 --> 01:04:42,597
With the passing of
each hour, the number of

820
01:04:42,609 --> 01:04:44,506
families forced from
their homes increases.

821
01:04:44,798 --> 01:04:46,216
♪

822
01:04:46,508 --> 01:04:51,888
Right now, the Cateura
landfill is totally flooded.

823
01:04:52,180 --> 01:04:57,143
This could lead to serious
environmental consequences.

824
01:05:10,115 --> 01:05:11,991
That used to be my house.

825
01:05:12,283 --> 01:05:16,454
♪

826
01:05:16,788 --> 01:05:19,751
When the rains began
and the river swelled,

827
01:05:19,763 --> 01:05:22,669
the water level began
rising very quickly.

828
01:05:22,961 --> 01:05:30,961
♪

829
01:05:35,932 --> 01:05:40,061
I had to sell all my pigs because
I have nowhere to keep them.

830
01:05:40,353 --> 01:05:45,233
♪

831
01:05:45,525 --> 01:05:48,611
That's where my instrument
workshop for the orchestra used to be.

832
01:05:48,903 --> 01:05:52,949
♪

833
01:05:53,241 --> 01:05:55,481
My greatest hope at the
moment is the Recycled Orchestra.

834
01:05:55,535 --> 01:06:03,535
♪

835
01:06:04,919 --> 01:06:08,590
We had to move like refugees
right next to the landfill.

836
01:06:14,220 --> 01:06:19,559
I was able to save this
can to make a violin.

837
01:06:19,851 --> 01:06:23,730
♪

838
01:06:24,022 --> 01:06:27,442
The flood is affecting
everyone here.

839
01:06:27,734 --> 01:06:30,069
My family is being affected...

840
01:06:30,361 --> 01:06:32,197
my relatives...

841
01:06:32,489 --> 01:06:33,489
my friends...

842
01:06:33,573 --> 01:06:35,700
♪

843
01:06:36,075 --> 01:06:38,161
And everyone I know
here in my neighborhood.

844
01:06:38,453 --> 01:06:43,625
♪

845
01:06:43,917 --> 01:06:49,297
It's really sad to see all of this in our
community where we live and grew up.

846
01:06:49,589 --> 01:06:53,218
♪

847
01:06:53,510 --> 01:06:56,095
The majority of the population
doesn't have anywhere to go.

848
01:06:56,387 --> 01:07:04,387
♪

849
01:07:12,362 --> 01:07:16,282
There are times when nature
can be so unforgiving with mankind.

850
01:07:16,574 --> 01:07:24,574
♪

851
01:07:26,751 --> 01:07:30,755
We're surrounded on all
four sides by rising water.

852
01:07:31,047 --> 01:07:33,675
We are about to be
flooded out of our home.

853
01:07:33,967 --> 01:07:36,219
We have to find a
way to get out of here.

854
01:07:38,471 --> 01:07:43,017
The flood is upsetting me a lot.

855
01:07:44,269 --> 01:07:46,344
When I see all of
the flooded homes...

856
01:07:46,356 --> 01:07:48,773
Especially my own...
it makes me really sad.

857
01:07:50,108 --> 01:07:52,610
To see people in the
streets asking for help.

858
01:07:52,902 --> 01:07:55,321
Those are baby clothes,
sweetheart. For a baby.

859
01:07:55,613 --> 01:08:00,243
♪

860
01:08:00,535 --> 01:08:05,164
There are many people that think only
of themselves and aren't willing to help.

861
01:08:06,416 --> 01:08:09,253
It's really tough to
leave your neighborhood

862
01:08:09,265 --> 01:08:11,337
where you were born and grew up.

863
01:08:11,629 --> 01:08:17,594
♪

864
01:08:17,885 --> 01:08:20,388
My mom is very
troubled by all this.

865
01:08:20,680 --> 01:08:23,057
She didn't want to
abandon our home.

866
01:08:23,349 --> 01:08:28,813
♪

867
01:08:29,105 --> 01:08:31,399
I've lost everything.

868
01:08:31,691 --> 01:08:33,818
I feel helpless. I
don't know what to do.

869
01:08:34,110 --> 01:08:35,361
♪

870
01:08:35,653 --> 01:08:37,742
For a while, the
water was rising very

871
01:08:37,754 --> 01:08:40,241
slowly, and then out
of nowhere it rushed in.

872
01:08:40,533 --> 01:08:42,744
♪

873
01:08:43,036 --> 01:08:45,163
And that's when I lost hope.

874
01:08:45,455 --> 01:08:47,749
I'll meet you there
on Wednesday, okay?

875
01:08:49,959 --> 01:08:53,755
We're trying to find housing options
for families of kids in the orchestra

876
01:08:54,047 --> 01:08:57,175
who have lost their
homes due to the flood.

877
01:09:00,887 --> 01:09:06,059
As an orchestra, we want to find a
new home for the affected families.

878
01:09:06,351 --> 01:09:14,351
♪

879
01:09:17,654 --> 01:09:20,708
When the water recede,
I'll carry everything

880
01:09:20,720 --> 01:09:23,159
to my house by
myself if I have to.

881
01:09:23,451 --> 01:09:25,912
♪

882
01:09:26,204 --> 01:09:29,999
No one can say,
"That woman is lazy."

883
01:09:30,291 --> 01:09:33,670
I work hard. I'm a fighter.

884
01:09:35,380 --> 01:09:37,382
I'm a fighter.

885
01:09:37,674 --> 01:09:39,592
I'll never abandon
this neighborhood.

886
01:09:39,884 --> 01:09:44,013
♪

887
01:09:44,305 --> 01:09:52,188
What worries me the most is my wife.
She is desperate to return to our house.

888
01:09:52,480 --> 01:09:57,652
I can't sleep at night, so I
pray to God and the Virgin Mary.

889
01:09:57,944 --> 01:10:00,780
♪

890
01:10:01,072 --> 01:10:03,658
I pray that the
floodwaters recede.

891
01:10:03,950 --> 01:10:06,703
That winds from the
south blow away the rains.

892
01:10:06,994 --> 01:10:14,994
♪

893
01:10:29,559 --> 01:10:35,440
For right now, the orchestra is
allowing us to stay in the school.

894
01:10:36,691 --> 01:10:43,531
If the orchestra had not allowed us to stay
here, we would be living on the streets.

895
01:10:43,823 --> 01:10:46,284
But living on the streets
is not a safe option.

896
01:10:46,576 --> 01:10:49,203
♪

897
01:10:49,495 --> 01:10:56,836
In the future, I'd like to find a
permanent home with my family.

898
01:10:57,128 --> 01:11:05,128
♪

899
01:11:41,172 --> 01:11:48,429
Good news. The level of the Paraguay
River decreased 3 cm in Asunción.

900
01:11:48,721 --> 01:11:51,265
And the water level
has stopped rising.

901
01:11:51,557 --> 01:11:54,727
For the first time since May, the
level of the Paraguay River is not rising.

902
01:11:55,019 --> 01:11:56,328
The floodwaters are
receding due to the

903
01:11:56,340 --> 01:11:57,831
decrease in the level
of the Paraguay River.

904
01:11:57,855 --> 01:12:02,485
♪

905
01:12:02,777 --> 01:12:07,323
The floodwaters were very
close to reaching my house.

906
01:12:07,615 --> 01:12:10,284
But we were very fortunate,
and our house did not flood.

907
01:12:10,576 --> 01:12:14,831
After nearly two and a half
months, the floodwaters are receding.

908
01:12:15,122 --> 01:12:18,209
Families are moving
back to their homes.

909
01:12:18,501 --> 01:12:21,212
This entire area is
starting to come back to life.

910
01:12:21,504 --> 01:12:24,465
♪

911
01:12:32,014 --> 01:12:40,014
♪

912
01:13:39,665 --> 01:13:44,712
We're going to do whatever it takes to
rebuild our homes and our neighborhood.

913
01:13:45,004 --> 01:13:48,549
♪

914
01:13:48,841 --> 01:13:50,509
I'll fight to the end.

915
01:13:50,801 --> 01:13:57,516
♪

916
01:13:57,808 --> 01:14:00,311
Let's take down
the " For Sale" sign.

917
01:14:02,688 --> 01:14:06,692
- Hold the ladder for me.
- Don't worry, I got it.

918
01:14:10,863 --> 01:14:13,032
Take this. It's for you to keep.

919
01:14:13,324 --> 01:14:19,664
The idea is for several families from
the orchestra to move here to live.

920
01:14:19,956 --> 01:14:24,043
The plan is for you
to move here directly.

921
01:14:24,335 --> 01:14:26,963
You won't be going
back to your old house.

922
01:14:27,254 --> 01:14:29,256
Do you agree with that plan?

923
01:14:29,548 --> 01:14:36,222
I'm always going to be by her
side. I'll always support and help her.

924
01:14:36,514 --> 01:14:42,353
Over there you can see the
landfill. And there is Colá's house.

925
01:14:42,645 --> 01:14:50,645
♪

926
01:15:08,713 --> 01:15:09,880
(laughing)

927
01:15:10,172 --> 01:15:18,172
♪

928
01:15:23,019 --> 01:15:25,604
Alright, let's see
what the problem is.

929
01:15:25,896 --> 01:15:27,982
We'll get this fixed in no time.

930
01:15:28,274 --> 01:15:32,028
Since we started making the instruments,
everyone in the neighborhood knows me.

931
01:15:32,319 --> 01:15:37,575
Kids say to me, " Don Colá,
can you make me a violin?"

932
01:15:37,867 --> 01:15:41,954
It makes me happy that all the kids
know who I am, and they appreciate me.

933
01:15:42,246 --> 01:15:44,248
♪

934
01:15:44,540 --> 01:15:45,541
There you go. All fixed.

935
01:15:45,833 --> 01:15:47,168
Thank you, Don Cola.

936
01:15:47,460 --> 01:15:49,545
Thank you. Don't forget
your bow, little fella.

937
01:15:49,837 --> 01:15:52,173
(softly playing violin)

938
01:16:03,142 --> 01:16:06,645
Very good. Just the last few
notes. Everyone play together now.

939
01:16:06,937 --> 01:16:10,149
(all playing together)

940
01:16:13,360 --> 01:16:14,862
Let's try it again.

941
01:16:16,989 --> 01:16:19,366
(all continue playing)

942
01:16:25,206 --> 01:16:30,086
♪

943
01:16:30,377 --> 01:16:33,464
My dream is to become a
professional violin teacher.

944
01:16:33,756 --> 01:16:36,467
I want to have lots of students
here from the community

945
01:16:36,759 --> 01:16:39,762
and give them the opportunity
to dream like I have had.

946
01:16:40,054 --> 01:16:43,682
♪

947
01:16:43,974 --> 01:16:47,228
In the future I'd like to be
a professional musician.

948
01:16:47,520 --> 01:16:52,233
I don't see myself
doing anything else.

949
01:16:52,525 --> 01:17:00,525
♪

950
01:17:03,077 --> 01:17:05,996
During all these years
with the orchestra,

951
01:17:06,288 --> 01:17:14,288
I've learned to value my friends, family,
and those who support what we are doing.

952
01:17:15,172 --> 01:17:16,757
Who can help me hang this tarp?

953
01:17:17,049 --> 01:17:18,843
♪

954
01:17:19,135 --> 01:17:22,346
We need to spread it
out and tie it up somehow.

955
01:17:22,638 --> 01:17:24,056
♪

956
01:17:24,348 --> 01:17:26,851
Use the wire to
hang it up there.

957
01:17:27,143 --> 01:17:35,143
♪

958
01:17:37,069 --> 01:17:38,112
Be careful, Colá!

959
01:17:38,404 --> 01:17:42,116
♪

960
01:17:42,408 --> 01:17:43,409
Done.

961
01:17:43,701 --> 01:17:46,078
♪

962
01:17:46,370 --> 01:17:49,832
- I bet they ate all the food.
- We'll be the scavengers.

963
01:17:50,124 --> 01:17:51,584
That's plenty.

964
01:17:51,876 --> 01:17:53,919
- Manioca?
- Yes.

965
01:17:54,211 --> 01:17:56,130
♪

966
01:17:56,422 --> 01:17:58,299
Just to let you all know,
I'm not going to cry.

967
01:17:58,591 --> 01:18:01,302
♪

968
01:18:01,594 --> 01:18:03,679
I'm not going to cry.

969
01:18:03,971 --> 01:18:09,560
Happy Birthday to
you! Tania! Tania!

970
01:18:09,852 --> 01:18:16,692
♪

971
01:18:16,984 --> 01:18:19,737
No! You're going to make me cry!

972
01:18:20,029 --> 01:18:23,532
(clapping and singing continues)

973
01:18:23,824 --> 01:18:31,824
♪

974
01:18:34,251 --> 01:18:36,879
Music is a unifying force.

975
01:18:37,171 --> 01:18:41,926
If you have talent,
and you work hard,

976
01:18:42,218 --> 01:18:44,058
it is possible to fulfill
your dreams in life.

977
01:18:47,556 --> 01:18:49,642
Hello, good evening.

978
01:18:49,934 --> 01:18:51,769
My name is Favio Chávez.

979
01:18:52,061 --> 01:18:58,609
I am the Recycled Instrument
Orchestra of Cateura conductor.

980
01:18:58,901 --> 01:19:00,819
Sorry my English finito.

981
01:19:01,111 --> 01:19:02,821
(laughter)

982
01:19:04,782 --> 01:19:08,077
Good evening. It's a
pleasure to be here.

983
01:19:08,369 --> 01:19:14,750
Our goal is to show that
culture is a basic human need.

984
01:19:16,043 --> 01:19:18,671
That music can change lives.

985
01:19:20,130 --> 01:19:27,471
And even when we live in the
most unfavorable conditions,

986
01:19:27,763 --> 01:19:30,349
we must never stop dreaming.

987
01:19:31,684 --> 01:19:36,522
To have nothing is not
an excuse to do nothing.

988
01:19:36,814 --> 01:19:37,940
Thank you very much.

989
01:19:38,232 --> 01:19:40,567
(applause)

990
01:19:44,321 --> 01:19:52,321
♪

991
01:21:16,455 --> 01:21:20,042
(cheering, applause)

992
01:21:26,507 --> 01:21:34,507
♪

993
01:21:43,982 --> 01:21:47,444
(singing in Spanish)

994
01:21:47,736 --> 01:21:55,736
♪

995
01:22:40,247 --> 01:22:42,207
♪ In the heart

996
01:22:42,499 --> 01:22:44,418
of our music ♪

997
01:22:44,710 --> 01:22:48,464
♪ There are echoes
each of us brings ♪

998
01:22:48,755 --> 01:22:52,259
♪ And the song of the world

999
01:22:52,551 --> 01:22:56,597
runs through us
all when we sing ♪

1000
01:22:56,889 --> 01:23:01,643
♪ Gives life to everything ♪

1001
01:23:01,935 --> 01:23:03,770
♪ Cateura ♪

1002
01:23:04,062 --> 01:23:06,023
♪ Come with me now ♪

1003
01:23:06,315 --> 01:23:07,691
♪ Cateura ♪

1004
01:23:07,983 --> 01:23:10,319
♪ Oh, how we will sing ♪

1005
01:23:10,611 --> 01:23:11,945
♪ Cateura ♪

1006
01:23:12,237 --> 01:23:15,157
♪ You gave us music ♪

1007
01:23:15,449 --> 01:23:19,411
♪ We give back the dream ♪♪

1008
01:23:19,703 --> 01:23:23,165
(singing in Spanish)

1009
01:23:23,457 --> 01:23:31,457
♪

